</iframe> </template>
</a>
</p>
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pzkNzkSqqic" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figure>
<p>Though most people are confident in the developer's pedigree and experience, having made a name for itself with the Hitman series, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/merry-christmas-james-bond-game-007-first-light-has-been-delayed">007: First Light faced a major delay in late 2025</a>. Earlier this year, the studio also caused confusion with <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/io-interactive-revises-and-reduces-007-first-light-pc-system-specs-after-gamers-highlight-inconsistencies-in-previous-versions">inconsistent PC system requirements</a>.</p><p>IO has had to build on its immersive sim and stealth expertise with cinematic and explosive action sequences for this game. In February, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/007-first-light-gameplay-director-talks-batman-arkham-and-uncharted-influences">gameplay director Andreas Krogh explained</a> how they'd looked at modern classics like <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/video-game-franchises/uncharted">Uncharted</a> and the <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/batman-arkham-games-order">Batman: Arkham</a> games for inspiration, so you could say 007: First Light has been properly shaken and not just stirred.</p>

